  "body": "<p>For this month's <a href=\"http://www.studiocalico.com/kits/front-row-scrapbook-kit?aff=6cc2c70f\">Main Kit</a> only layout at <a href=\"http://www.studiocalico.com/shop/new?aff=6cc2c70f\">Studio Calico</a>, I tried to push myself to try new techniques with common supplies.</p>\n\n\n\n\n\n\n<figure>\n\n\n<img src=\"https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/5dd0ae59b4b4b35c07faf907/1600129648459-EKP730ZJAQZTR3Q0AM76/2a%3DDSC_1109-600x398.jpg\"/>\n\n\n<figcaption>\n<p>I started out by stitching three arrows with white embroidery floss.</p>\n</figcaption>\n</figure>\n\n\n\n<figure>\n\n\n<img src=\"https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/5dd0ae59b4b4b35c07faf907/1600129673223-LMVKPTA490FQZHQZCLG7/2b-DSC_1110-600x398.jpg\"/>\n\n\n<figcaption>\n<p>Next, I added a few droplets of Calico White Mister Huey.</p>\n</figcaption>\n</figure>\n\n\n\n<figure>\n\n\n<img src=\"https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/5dd0ae59b4b4b35c07faf907/1600129688073-NR2AXP6MBQU7XB0RTOXC/2c-DSC_1111-600x398.jpg\"/>\n\n\n</figure>\n\n\n\n<figure>\n\n\n<img src=\"https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/5dd0ae59b4b4b35c07faf907/1600129716750-JQ94FQRHMZW5TKTTS48C/2d-.jpg\"/>\n\n\n<figcaption>\n<p>From there, I arranged my photo, patterned paper, and embellishments to my liking and secured them down.</p>\n</figcaption>\n</figure>\n\n\n\n<figure>\n\n\n<img src=\"https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/5dd0ae59b4b4b35c07faf907/1600129735102-KUF0RRM12JTHV6DSU52R/2e-DSC_1113-600x398.jpg\"/>\n\n\n<figcaption>\n<p>Then I placed a strip of that awesome ombre washi tape onto a scrap piece of white cardstock and cut out a couple of hearts to place around my page.</p>\n</figcaption>\n</figure>\n\n\n\n<figure>\n\n\n<img src=\"https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/5dd0ae59b4b4b35c07faf907/1600129752284-TBCGXLSHZPJXY70R4ES8/2f-DSC_1114-600x398.jpg\"/>\n\n\n</figure>\n\n\n\n<figure>\n\n\n<img src=\"https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/5dd0ae59b4b4b35c07faf907/1600129767463-7FBH0DL8PDV077NM6UMW/2g-DSC_1115-600x398.jpg\"/>\n\n\n<figcaption>\n<p>After the hearts were glued down (using a mix of dimensional adhesive and a tape runner), I cut out a row of arrows from the SC patterned paper and placed it on the page.</p>\n</figcaption>\n</figure>\n\n\n\n<figure>\n\n\n<img src=\"https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/5dd0ae59b4b4b35c07faf907/1600129784143-CASNA6E6BSAKB8RRESPV/2h-DSC_1116-600x398.jpg\"/>\n\n\n<figcaption>\n<p>Using the American Crafts' cardstock letter stickers, I spelled out my title and determined it was done!</p>\n</figcaption>\n</figure>\n\n\n\n<figure>\n\n\n<img src=\"https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/5dd0ae59b4b4b35c07faf907/1600129815421-DI38Z57C9IBZMGOQC4LM/image-asset.jpeg\"/>\n\n\n</figure>\n\n\n\n<figure>\n\n\n<img src=\"https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/5dd0ae59b4b4b35c07faf907/1600129826309-11LJSPQ20V47ODJ1G19A/2j-proof-562x600.jpg\"/>\n\n\n<figcaption>\n<p>You can see more of my layouts from this month's kit <a href=\"http://www.studiocalico.com/creative-team-gallery/front-row/scrapbook/amy-tan--2?aff=6cc2c70f\">right here</a>!</p>\n</figcaption>\n</figure>"
}